4:
MY LORD calls upon me again,
granting me a new mission—one
which will see my grand desire
realized!
8:
That mission? To retrieve an
ANCIENT ARTIFACT, long interred in
sand, lying in wait deep within a
distant desert!
13:
That's the plot summary for your
next adventure, I take it?
20:
I mean... I feel like we need one!
Don't you think the mood in
Starview's been a bit... dour? Given
the whole business with the
Overlords...
30:
Oh, sorry, I wasn't blaming you!
Please don't make that pouty face,
Stella, I can't take it!
33:
Anyway... I get that the situation is
dire, but it's not like we can do
anything about it NOW, right?
36:
So I figured... we could use a
diversion! A breather! Some fun and
games!
41: You know what? I think Denah's right.
45:
Let's take some time off and go on
an adventure!
50:
Okay!
Please take us along, Denah.
54:
Leave it to me! My Lord's all-seeing
Phantom Eye has already glimpsed
the scorching, sandstorm-ravaged
land to which we head!
57:
You but need to follow behind
me—as obedient goslings cling to
their mother—and you will not go
astray!
61:
...Yeah, we'd better not. Getting lost
in the desert is a death
sentence—you won't be able to
survive there for a month like you
did in Oceanus, you know.
66:
I-I know that! Sonia told me as
much.
Don't worry, we'll be fine—mainly
because I've decided YOU'RE going
to be our guide!
70:
Okay. But, uh, are you really going to
head into a desert with clothes like
that?
74:
What do you mean? This new outfit
is perfect for a devoted servant of
darkness like myself!
78: I suppose it does look pretty stylish...
82:
Aha! So there IS a part of you that
longs for darkness... 
You know, you'd look pretty good 
in black too, Alk—why don't you 
get a similar outfit?!
90:
Besides, aren't you hot wearing
something like that?
95:
Nope! This shields my skin from the
sun's rays. Plus, I got an alchemist to
outfit it with special heat
resistance—cost an arm and a leg,
though...
98:
This garb is capable of withstanding
even dragon's breath! Well, it better
be—if it doesn't, that alchemist is
getting a beating...
109:
Hate to say I told you so, but...
Here, need some water?
119:
The plan is to explore some ancient
ruins, no? Once we're inside, things
should cool down considerably.
124:
Really?! Then what are we waiting
for? Let's go! My destiny awaits!
129:
Denah, stop!
That's the wrong way!
138:
Hmm... Give me a sec here. That
rune means "a", and that one is "d",
so given the context... It's gotta be
this one!
143: Hold on—you can read this script?
146:
Yeah. I just thought it'd be cool to be
able to read an ancient language,
you know?
150:
Hah! I'm not one to balk in the face
of a minor challenge like reading
ancient glyphs!
154:
You... studied a language from an
ancient civilization—from another
world, mind you—all because it
would be "cool"? That's... honestly
impressive.
158:
Yeah, but you know what I think is
even more interesting? All the
different magic systems they have
on other worlds! They all just make
my head spin!
162: You really are quite talented, Denah.
169:
Are you members of the Golden
Dawn? Or do you hail from the
Kingdom?
171:
It doesn't matter who they are,
Brother. We can't let the relic fall into
their hands!
174: Wait! This is all a misunderstanding—
178:
Let's be real here—you guys are just
here for the treasure as well, right?
180:
The history that lies buried within
these sands... The likes of you do not
deserve to have it!
182:
Yep, with a lame comeback like that,
now I'm convinced.
185:
You guys are all high-and-mighty
about it, but basically you're just
exploring ruins to search for goodies.
188:
Meaning, we're not so different. Let
me put it to you in a way you can
understand...
191:
If a fight with me and my Lord is
what you desire, then so be it!
Come, grave robbers!
194:
But beware—the darkness that 
I wield stems from the farthest
depths of the abyss! Can you stand
undaunted before the might of the
VOID?
200:
Er, well... That's no good.
How about a temporary truce?
208:
Our village is just to the west of here.
If you are ever in need of something,
come see us.
210:
Heathen or not, we swear to repay
this debt to you.
213:
Was that truly the right call? They
ended up leaving with the treasure...
217:
Pfft, it's no problem. That thing didn't
look like it was going to be of any
use to me on my quest anyway!
220:
More importantly than that, we've
gotta decide where we're going next!
224:
Man, nothing gets you down, does
it? I guess you're gonna need a
chaperone and guide on your next
outing too, huh?
229:
You bet I will! Let's all go somewhere
together! This was SO much fun, 
I want to do it again!
238:
Okay! Then it's settled.
We're off to our next adventure!
